<br>
My management body consisted of me, raid commander, Cassia, backup commander and buffing line coordinator, Lothax, loot coordinator and attendance taker, Dogedme, attendance taker, Belce back up commander and secondary assist, Rbecka, main assist and puller, and Muji, feign death puller and stunt crash test dummy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  These guys did an awesome job! Also thanks to my group leaders, Rbecka, Zeol, Luolana, Eressia, Draeven, Cassia, Lothax, Baptismo, Flarren and Dogedme, who all did quite well at keeping me informed. We moved quickly through the dungeon to the  king room, bound, buffed a little and began killing ice giants. We were a bit unruly at first, not pulling the ice giants back to a spot where we could fight them effectively, but soon had the gate clear and set up for pulls from around the lair. Rbecka started pulling from the north hallway, and did a fine job of clearing the hallway. Flarren made a good suggestion at this point, which we'll use again. We formed a U shape around this tunnel and let the puller come into the center of the room with the mob, then close ranks around it, to keep the giants from warping through walls. <br>
<br>
Once the hallway was clear to the ramp, I sent Muji the monk in to began FD pulling to clear the lair. Though inexperienced, he jumped at the task and moved in. However, on his first pull, an icy terror gave him the business end of a force blast, which drove him into a pit and down into the tunnels below Vox's lair. I believe that this caused a train to form, which actually ended up helping us. Before we knew it, we had 6 ice giants on us (and we were unprepared). Here I must point out that though discipline slipped a bit, we accomplished some an AMAZING feat. Of the 6, 2 were priests, 1 was a magus, 1 was a priest of Nagafen and there were 3 regular ice giants. We fought long and hard, charming some of the priests to help our cause, and in the end we triumphed with only 1 death. There was some early confusion about what mob to hit, and confusion about some charmed mobs, but we recovered and killed them all, an outstanding job. <br>
<br>
At this point I began trying to talk Muji in. He was unfamiliar with the pit area, but remained patient, making his way slowly back up to Vox's lair. As he was coming up, I looked into the hallway outside the lair and saw that Vox was stuck in the doorway. The last 3 guilds that failed on Vox had failed because she became stuck in the doorway, and no one could hit her or cast on her. I became immediately worried and petitioned for her to be moved back to her spot. This petition was never answered. Meanwhile, Muji had made it up to the boulder and Feigned, at which point he was right under Vox, so he camped to clear aggro. Vox was still stuck in the doorway however. When he came back, he got to the camp and I hit upon an idea to get her out of the doorway. <br>
<br>
I had Muji walk up to her and target and hit her once, then FD immediately, with instructions to camp out if necessary. This is akin to asking him to go up and box her on the nose and see if she kills him, but he never even blinked. That's the kind of self-sacrifice I love to see on these raids. As soon as he touched her, she aggroed not only him, but all of us. The signs of AE fear popped up all around us (scaring the mess out of those first-timer dragon raid attendees). I immediately had us camp out to clear the aggro. When we returned, Muji made it safely back, and I checked the doorway. To my joyous surprise, the beast had returned to her lair, paving the way for our assault. <br>
<br>
We moved up and quickly began the buffing line, run quite ably by Cassia. We buffed quickly, and I used our main tank group as guards over the buff line, saving their buffs until last so that we could handle any Ice Giant respawns. This was a good idea, as we had a couple, one of which managed to summon and kill Belce. We got him ressed and got camped out, made it to the chat room and waited. When Cassia finally gave us the all clear, we moved in and took up positions on the ramp, raring to go. With a shout of &quot;1 2 3 GO GO GO&quot; I sent the raiders in, charging madly along. <br>
<br>
Having instructed the tanks not to attack her until they were on her pedastel, we started out well enough, drawing Vox back to the middle of her lair to avoid her getting stuck in walls. But as the fight progressed, she moved closer and closer to the door, and sometime after sending in the casters, she took up her permanent place near the door and began striking through the wall at our healing line. On this raid, we managed to get 6 bards, and did they ever make the difference! For my own experience, having the bard magic and cold resist songs playing made me almost un fearable. I only got feared for a length of about 4 seconds once, the rest were negligible. I'm not sure how much damage her breath weapon did though. I only went back for heals one time, and was quickly and efficiently healed. Heading back in, I realized she was close to going down, and was reaching through the wall to attack our healers. Since I could still hit her, I shouted for no one to back off, to make sure we stayed on her, and watched her hit points go farther and farther down. Suddenly I realized I was at 1 bubble of health again and ran back for a heal. The doorway was so clogged, I finally gave up and decided to just stay on her, whether I died or not. I kept slashing and poking away, and just as I died to her last breath attack, I saw her health bar with no visible red. Popping back up in Qeynos, I got the report that she had died! WOOOOOT!<br>
<br>
My first of 3 linkdeaths occured then, right as I zoned out of Qeynos. Upon returning to the game, I found myself in Qeynos Hills, somewhere above it, at about the level of Plane of Sky apparently. Hoping a camp out would help, I did so, then returned to find myself in the same place. I began to look all around, as all I could see was gray (had the sky turned off). Suddenly below me the ground appeared and rose to meet me.... BAM! You have fallen for 10000 points of damage, Loading... Please Wait... AAAAAAAGHHHHH!!<br>
<br>
One tip for those this happens to... type /report immediately or you will never get a res from a GM. I didn't, and had a friend petition for me, as my previous petition was somehow still in the Queue (but still unanswered... go figure). Thank you Verant... /rude Verant Customer Service.<br>
<br>
Upon being ressed, I got my corpse and began the long corpse recovery. We got the paladins ressed first (so they could roll on the book of scale), and had 5 or 6 bodies in the pit. I sent Dogedme to the pit to get bodies, and he was overwhelmed when his invis wore off. I then sent Guppin, who managed to get a few corpses before going LD (from which he never returned). Dogedme returned to the corpse recovery and eventually got everyone out. At this point, most people were patient. We still had a few who tried to rush us into lottoing for things, and I have to tell you, this is uncalled for. I have to work in the mornings too, there are other people there who have to work or go to school, and they were patient and never bothered me. One person gave me no less than 10 tells about one item. Be patient, sit down, and be quiet or log off and don't get any rolls. Simple as that. It's rude, it only seeks to slow down the corpse recovery, which slows down the process of rolling. There were somewhere in the neighborhood of 15-20 bodies to either res or pull from the pit, and you are no more important than any of those people just because you have to work, I only got 3 hours of sleep myself. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Nuff said. <br>
<br>
