<br>
I've been on 2 Vox raids and one Naggy raid with CoG, and we're 3 for 3 when I'm along! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
Amazingly I didn't die this time.  Having a bard pump my CR up to almost 200 probably didn't hurt!  So not only was I able to keep fighting and do a more damage (as well as chain cast stun between whacks), I got to see a dragon DIE this time, not just see it's body afterwards... I love it!  This was definitely one of the better raids I've been on, thanks everyone.<br>
<br>
As for falling in pits, I got feared twice, and with DMF on and my screen &quot;aimed&quot; at dead level (I hit the 'home' button before going in) I didn't fall into the pits, but lingered above them until I could return and start whacking the big lizard once more.  The last Vox raid my screen was &quot;aimed&quot; slightly downward which caused me to run down one of the pits before the fear wore off, despite DMF still being on.<br>
So, from my experience, while fear makes you run at a constant speed and controls the horizontal path, it doesn't control your verticle direction (ie, you will still &quot;dive&quot; at the ground if you are aimed that way when feared, but won't if you aren't).  Definitely something I'll keep in mind in the future.<br>
<br>
Also of note: the polar bears and wolves in the pits are probably considered animals, but the spiders are most likely not...  so Invis vs. Animals might postpone death, I don't know that it would actually make getting out of the pit alive possible. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
 <p>-Kommisar Nils "Can-Head" Hansen -- Guild Officer. Master Smith. Tank.
